Erdogan’s Party Has 47% of Vote Before Election, Sabah Reports

-- B y   E m r e   P e k e r
-- 
2011-06-02T05:57:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/erdogan-s-party-has-47-of-vote-before-election-sabah-reports.html
Prime Minister  Recep Tayyip Erdogan ’s
Justice and Development Party may win 47 percent of the vote in
an election next week, Sabah said citing a survey by Pollmark.  The main opposition  Republican People’s Party  has 25
percent support and the Nationalist Action Party 12.6 percent,
the newspaper reported. The pro-Kurdish Peace and Democracy
Party might get 6.5 percent of the votes, it said.  Pollmark conducted its survey of 5,325 people from May 21
through May 27, Sabah said. The polling firm distributed the
votes for undecided voters, who made up 11 percent of
participants. The newspaper didn’t provide a margin of error.  Click here for web link  To contact the reporter on this story:
